name: Lakers
summary: The Denver Nuggets have taken a commanding 3-0 lead in their NBA playoff series against the Los Angeles Lakers. After losing Game 1 in overtime, the Nuggets rallied to win Game 2 in Los Angeles before earning a 112-105 victory in Game 3 at home. The Lakers, led by LeBron James, were unable to keep up with the Nuggets' high-powered offense, which was led by Nikola Jokic's 30 points and 13 rebounds. The Nuggets are now one win away from advancing to the second round of the playoffs, while the Lakers face elimination in Game 4 on Monday.
